description:
&lt;p&gt;***NUH APPLICANT&#39;S ONLY***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;INTERNAL VACANCY ONLY therefore only current employees of Nottingham University Hospitals NHS trust will be considered for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 Registered Nurse to join our Surgical Capacity and Flow Team for a period of 9 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, calm and organised person who can adapt very quickly to changing situations.&lt;br /&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills are essential and you must have a flexible attitude to work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must possess a solid understanding of discharge processes within the trust, be competent in the use of Nerve Centre bed management system and feel confident in&lt;br /&gt;completing daily reports by pulling information from various computer systems.&lt;br /&gt;Experience of managing capacity and flow is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The role will not only involve acting as ‘Bronze’- an escalation point for capacity and flow&lt;br /&gt;issues within the division, but the appointee will also support the Capacity and Flow Matron in educating our wards on discharge management and on nights will act as a Senior Contact not only for Capacity issues but also Staffing and guidance for any other issues that may arise on the wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Please remember that you must have sought your manager’s permission to be released for the secondment before applying.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Victoria Loffreda, Surgical Capacity and Flow matron Ext 61406&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or one of our Current Team leaders on 07812270096.&lt;/p&gt;
